Chakra UI v3 — Phase 2 Recipe Convention
=========================================

This directory documents the canonical recipe pattern established in Phase 2
for all subsequent phases (3-5) to follow.

PATTERN SUMMARY
---------------

1. Component base
   Use the Chakra v3 component (Button, Input, etc.) as the rendering root.
   Never fall back to a raw HTML element for styled interactive components.

2. Variant mapping
   Map our variant/size prop values to Chakra's built-in recipe variants.
   Use a switch/VariantProps object literal, not className strings or cva().
   Example: variant="ghost" → Chakra variant="plain" + bg/color token overrides.

3. Token application
   Use semantic token names from apps/web/src/theme/system.ts as Chakra style props.
   Examples:
     bg="accent.default"         (Linear blue — resolves to ~#2A6FDB in light mode)
     color="fg.default"          (primary text)
     borderColor="border.default" (subtle border)
     bg="bg.sunken"              (input / card surface)
   Never hardcode oklch() or hex values in component files.

4. API preservation
   Exported TypeScript interface must match the previous implementation exactly.
   Internal implementation may change completely; the public contract must not.
   This ensures zero changes needed in consuming pages, gallery, or domain components.

5. "use client" placement
   Add 'use client' at the top of any component that uses Chakra interactive
   primitives (Button, Switch, Checkbox, etc.) — these use Ark UI internally
   which relies on React context and browser events.
   Read-only display components (Badge, Card) do not need "use client".

6. a11y — preserved behaviours
   - IconButton: aria-label is required (TypeScript-enforced via interface)
   - Input/Textarea: label + error wired via Field.Root (aria-invalid, aria-describedby automatic)
   - Checkbox: indeterminate → checked="indeterminate" → aria-checked="mixed" (Ark UI)
   - Switch: role="switch" + aria-checked managed by SwitchRoot (Ark UI)
   - RadioGroup: role="radio" per item, keyboard arrow-key navigation (Ark UI)
   - Select: uses NativeSelect for options-array API → native browser a11y

FILE LOCATIONS
--------------
  Primitives (Phase 2):
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/Button.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/IconButton.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/Input.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/Textarea.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/Select.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/Checkbox.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/Radio.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/primitive/Switch.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/Badge.tsx
    apps/web/src/components/ui/Card.tsx

  Token system:
    apps/web/src/theme/system.ts       (createSystem config — SSoT)
    apps/web/src/theme/provider.tsx    (ChakraProvider + next-themes wiring)

PHASES 3-5 CHECKLIST
---------------------
For each new component migration, verify:
  [ ] Chakra component used as base (not raw HTML)
  [ ] variant/size mapped via switch literal with token props
  [ ] semantic tokens used exclusively (no raw values)
  [ ] exported TS interface unchanged from previous version
  [ ] "use client" present if component uses hooks/events
  [ ] aria-* attributes delegated to Chakra/Ark (not hand-rolled)
  [ ] test rewritten to assert behavior + aria, not className strings
